prompt:
Seven panelists — Pia, Quon, Rho, Sef, Tovi, Ume, and Vail — are to be seated in a single row of 7 chairs numbered 1 through 7, one panelist per chair. A seating must satisfy ALL of the following constraints:
(a) Pia and Quon do not sit in adjacent chairs (chair numbers differing by 1);
(b) Rho sits in a lower-numbered chair than Sef;
(c) Tovi sits in neither chair 1 nor chair 7;
(d) Ume and Vail sit in adjacent chairs.

How many distinct seatings satisfy all four constraints? Give the exact integer inside \boxed{}.
